You are The Devil

Materiality. Material Force. Material temptation; sometimes obsession

The Devil is often a great card for business success; hard work and ambition.

Perhaps the most misunderstood of all the major arcana, the Devil is not really "Satan" at all, but Pan the half-goat nature god and/or Dionysius. These are gods of pleasure and abandon, of wild behavior and unbridled desires. This is a card about ambitions; it is also synonymous with temptation and addiction. On the flip side, however, the card can be a warning to someone who is too restrained, someone who never allows themselves to get passionate or messy or wild - or ambitious. This, too, is a form of enslavement. As a person, the Devil can stand for a man of money or erotic power, aggressive, controlling, or just persuasive. This is not to say a bad man, but certainly a powerful man who is hard to resist. The important thing is to remember that any chain is freely worn. In most cases, you are enslaved only because you allow it.

Find your own pose!

Cliffhanger Traits and Tendencies On the surface, the Cliffhanger might seem like an angry pose, the aftermath of a heated argument or years of misunderstanding. Really the pose is an elegant expression of two people in sublime agreement about the supremacy of personal comfort. Both parties believe that when it comes to getting a good night's sleep, the sides of the bed are its most prime real estate, and both are practical enough to recognize that the only way for everyone to get the best of the bed is to split up. Comfort Zone The Cliffhanger is a Sea Sleeper pose. Other Sea poses a Cliffhanger might try include The Bubble Blower and Sixth Posture of the Perfumed Forest. Point of Interest The Cliffhanger pose is the ideal arrangement for couples sharing the bed with an infant or injured animal, with the safety frame of soft humanity that they create together providing a natural "crib bumper."

How evil are you?
The Survivalist
Survival: 68%, Group Survival: 67%, Confidence: 50%, Integrity: 54%
You do whatever it takes to survive, to keep on going. If it means leaving someone behind, so be it. You don't have much in the way of bravery though, you'll run away if it feels like the smarter choice. You really don't give a shit about the world or other people but because of your wise choices and survivalistic instinct; everyone around you has a much better chance of survival. You protect your few true friends to the death but that is your only moral saving grace. Often the 'Anti-Hero', a good example is Riddick in Pitch Black. His primary concern is getting himself out alive, no matter the cost. He proves he isn't emotionless in the end, saving a few friends instead of abandoning them to garentee his own escape. In a horror movie you will shine cold and ruthless for the better half of the film but in the end save someone you care about.

I collected about $3200 this fortnight so I was finally able to put something decent in my savings.

Work is kinda boring since there isn't really anything I can do and what I could do I did in like a few hours.  Folded and prepared like a billion schematics for the substations around the place.
Though this morning a cooked a BBQ at work with lamb chops, bacon and sausages.  Was great.

Don't know what I'm gunna do for the next few weeks.

Went and saw superman today and it was alright.  Lois isn't very good looking at all and the actors are about as good as the 1970s ones.  Though as always Kevin Spacey was awesome.  Its worth seeing.

I have to say what is the world coming to when you can't even get those multi-coloured wafers that you put in the ice cream sundaes.  I could find everything else but not those.  Crazy crazy world.

Well been so long since I posted something I decided (sorta) to post something. I'm totally out of my trial period and almost to the stage where I'm allowd to go near live stuff. Second part not so great since one of my instructors seems to think its great to tell us all (often) that we are in the highest suicide bracket. Crazy TAFE people. Only one more week of them and its back to work finally. Still TAFE is easy and I'm making honors easy, making about 90%+ average. Long weekend worked out great even if I have to bank my RDO. Had another of the multitude of 21st's on saturday night. Crazy one with a pool table, fooz ball table, table tennis table and a jumping castle. It rained a fair bit though so most people including be got soaked on the castle. Fair few drunk gals running round doing and shouting crazy stuff. Got another 21st invite there too so I still got another 2 in the bank. Sunday was a BarBQ at a work mates house with some mates where I got to meet their missuses (crazy word) and find out all the great stories that they bring home about me. Oddly less then I thought in some areas and more in others. Was a fairly long drive though and I hadn't been there before so was a tricky drive going 110kms/hour and reading a map at the same time especially come home when it was dark. Funilly enough I met my first toll (while I was driving) and the first time I threw change in I missed with some of it. Today (Monday) went and saw The Omen, it sucked....... just kidding it was pretty good but I haven't seen the originals. Thought we might have got told off by some people for laughing so loud but noone did. We couldn't help it though, some of that movie is just hilarious. Will hopefully have more to say later. Cya
